  "text": "In order to capture the variance of the trajectories, we introduce a distribution p(w; θ) over the weight vector w, with parameters θ. In most cases, the distribution p(w; θ) will be Gaussian where the parameter vector θ = {µ w , Σ w } specifies the mean and the variance of w. However, also more complex distributions such as Gaussian mixture models can be used for this task [CITATION_1] . The trajectory distribution p(τ ; θ) can now be computed by marginalizing out the weight vector w, i.e.",
